The paper proposes a secure localization algorithm for IoT devices using Blockchain technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with networking and communication between IoT devices, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of Blockchain technology also involves distributed computing, which can be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for localization, which can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses simulation results to evaluate the proposed algorithm, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
